# ============================================================
# What never gets uploaded to Vercel.
#
# Applies to CLI uploads (`vercel`, `vercel build`). The Git integration
# ignores this file and uses the repo contents instead, so anything that
# must never ship has to be gitignored as well.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES — why vercel.json says what it says.
#
# They live here because vercel.json is validated against a strict JSON
# schema: it permits neither comments nor unknown keys, so a deploy fails
# outright if you try to annotate it in place.
#
# 1. ROUTING. The build emits a real directory per route
#    (dist/price/index.html and 29 siblings). Vercel checks the filesystem
#    BEFORE applying `rewrites`, so /price is served from its prerendered
#    file and never reaches the SPA fallback — which is what would silently
#    replace 30 crawlable pages with an empty shell. The fallback source is
#    deliberately `/((?!.*\.).*)`: only extensionless paths fall through to
#    index.html, so a missing image or script still returns an honest 404
#    instead of HTML with a 200. Note that after prerendering, dist/index.html
#    IS the homepage, so an unknown URL renders the homepage markup and then
#    swaps to the client-side 404 — a soft 404, acceptable here because every
#    real route is prerendered.
#
# 2. trailingSlash:false matches the canonicals <Seo> emits (no trailing
#    slash). Vercel 308-redirects /price/ to /price, so there is one URL per
#    page and the canonical always agrees with what the server serves.
#
# 3. CSP. Derived from what the app actually loads:
#      script-src   self + googletagmanager/google-analytics (gtag, only when
#                   VITE_GA_ID is set). NO 'unsafe-inline', NO 'unsafe-eval' —
#                   the production bundle contains zero eval/new Function
#                   (verified against dist/assets/index-*.js), and GSAP,
#                   Framer Motion, Lenis and Leaflet all run fine without it.
#                   The prerendered <script type="application/ld+json"> blocks
#                   are data, not executable scripts: the HTML spec abandons
#                   "prepare the script" before the CSP inline check for
#                   non-JavaScript types, and even in a browser that reported
#                   a violation the element stays in the DOM, so structured
#                   data survives either way.
#      style-src    self + 'unsafe-inline' — a real concession, made
#                   knowingly. The prerendered HTML is a Chrome DOM dump, so
#                   every inline style React, GSAP and Leaflet wrote is baked
#                   into the markup as a literal style="…" attribute. Hashes
#                   cannot cover values that change per render, and a nonce
#                   needs a server to mint one per request — this is a static
#                   site, so there is none. 'unsafe-inline' for styles is the
#                   only option that keeps the site looking right; it is much
#                   weaker than script 'unsafe-inline' but it is not free.
#      connect-src  BOTH script.google.com and script.googleusercontent.com.
#                   The Apps Script endpoint 302s to the latter and CSP
#                   re-checks every redirect hop — drop either origin and
#                   lead capture dies silently.
#      img-src      self + images.pexels.com (indicative stock via
#                   src/lib/images.js) + *.basemaps.cartocdn.com (the CARTO
#                   dark_all tiles Leaflet loads in LivingMap).
#      font-src     self only — @fontsource ships the woff2 files into
#                   /assets, so there is no external font origin.
#
# 4. PERMISSIONS-POLICY. autoplay and fullscreen are allowed for self: the
#    hero video autoplays and FloorPlan calls requestFullscreen. Geolocation
#    is denied — the map uses hardcoded coordinates and the site never asks
#    the browser where you are.
#
# 5. CACHING. /assets/* is content-hashed by Vite, so it is immutable for a
#    year. /renders and the brochure PDF keep stable filenames and can be
#    replaced in place, so they revalidate hourly and lean on the edge +
#    stale-while-revalidate. HTML revalidates on every request so copy
#    changes appear immediately.
#
# 6. PRERENDERING DOES NOT RUN ON VERCEL. buildCommand is `npm run build`
#    (plain vite build), NOT `npm run build:static` — scripts/prerender.mjs
#    drives a real Chrome binary and Vercel's build image has none. Deploying
#    as configured ships the SPA WITHOUT the 30 prerendered pages. See the
#    handover notes for the two ways to fix this (bundle a Chromium and set
#    CHROME_PATH, or prerender in CI and `vercel deploy --prebuilt`).
# ============================================================

# --- Never build from, or upload, these ---
node_modules
.git
.github
.vercel

# Build output. Vercel builds from source; shipping a stale dist/ would
# deploy yesterday's site.
dist
dist-ssr

# --- Secrets. Env vars belong in the Vercel dashboard, never in an upload. ---
.env
.env.*
*.local
*.pem

# --- Repo furniture with no place in a deployment ---
# Anchored, and NOT a blanket *.md: src/content/blog/*.md is real content,
# inlined at build time by import.meta.glob(..., "?raw") in src/lib/blog.js.
# Ignoring markdown wholesale would build a site with six empty blog posts.
/README.md
.oxlintrc.json
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# --- Oversized media ---
# 103 MB source master, already gitignored and referenced by nothing —
# Hero plays the compressed /hero-brabus.mp4. Uploading it would blow past
# Vercel's per-file limit and add nothing.
public/BrabusIslandVilla_H264_WEB.mp4
